Madagascar's cocoa production isestimated 13 pct higher this year at 2,720 tonnes, up from2,400 in 1986, Agriculture Ministry officials said.    This improvement reflects the government's efforts over thelast seven years to extend existing cocoa plantations and plantnew higher yielding varieties, particularly at the northern tipof the island, they said.    Last year, Madagascar exported 2,189 tonnes of high qualitycocoa, up from 1,624 in 1985, the Trade Ministry said.    This year's exports are estimated at 2,400 tonnes. Reuter&#3;